1
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:04,100
Spring is almost here, isn't it?

2
00:00:04,100 --> 00:00:06,170
Yeah, spring...

3
00:00:06,170 --> 00:00:07,940
It's really spring.

4
00:00:07,940 --> 00:00:11,810
When spring approaches,
we tend to mellow out, don't we?

5
00:00:11,810 --> 00:00:14,710
You're always mellow, though.

6
00:00:14,710 --> 00:00:17,910
It's more unusual when you're not mellow.

7
00:00:17,910 --> 00:00:20,780
Now that you mention it, you're right.

8
00:00:25,420 --> 00:00:32,590
"Dear Ai, this year's Carnevale
brought more visitors than usual."

9
00:00:32,590 --> 00:00:36,390
"Things were really lively right up
until yesterday, when it ended."

10
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:43,870
"During Carnevale, we had many opportunities
to work onboard our mentors' gondolas."

11
00:00:43,870 --> 00:00:50,970
"It gave us the chance to watch them up close
as they worked with all sorts of customers."

12
00:00:51,780 --> 00:00:56,680
"It was a great hands-on
learning experience. But..."

13
00:00:56,680 --> 00:01:01,090
"...on the other hand, it also made me
very aware of my shortcomings."

14
00:01:01,320 --> 00:01:04,780
"I guess I still have a long way to go
before I can become a Prima."

15
00:01:05,730 --> 00:01:08,160
"I'm sure you'll be just fine, Akari."

16
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:14,260
"In fact, by the next time I visit Neo-Venezia,
you might already be a Prima."

17
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:33,990
Do you remember that day
Oboeteimasuka ano hi o

18
00:01:36,790 --> 00:01:44,290
When your heart suddenly began to race
Futo kanjita tokimeki o

19
00:01:47,740 --> 00:01:53,810
The rays from the blue sky were pouring over you...
Aoi hizashi abite

20
00:01:53,810 --> 00:01:57,580
...as you cut through the wind
Kaze o kiru kimi ni

21
00:01:57,580 --> 00:02:05,090
I couldn't look away, and when our eyes met
Mitoreru to me ga atte

22
00:02:05,090 --> 00:02:09,490
I couldn't help but smile
Egao koboreta

23
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:14,930
It's just like a spiral
Marude supiraare

24
00:02:14,930 --> 00:02:23,390
I want to spend my days waving to you
Itsumademo te o furitai hibi

25
00:02:24,740 --> 00:02:33,410
This is my proof that I was here with you
Koko ni tashika ni kimi to ita akashi

26
00:02:33,410 --> 00:02:37,420
An eternal spiral
Zutto supiraare

27
00:02:37,420 --> 00:02:47,200
There's a path which stretches on ahead
Kono saki mo tsuzuiteru michi ga aru

28
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:56,340
When you climb the next hill,
Tsugi no saka o nobottara

29
00:02:56,340 --> 00:03:00,800
Let's meet again
Mata aimashou

30
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:12,840
That Imminent Spring Breeze...

31
00:03:16,930 --> 00:03:19,160
Gondola coming through!

32
00:03:19,230 --> 00:03:22,600
Wow, Junior! You're really
projecting your voice today.

33
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:25,160
That was amazing, Alice!

34
00:03:25,230 --> 00:03:27,240
I had a revelation.

35
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,430
Oh?

36
00:03:30,270 --> 00:03:35,230
While watching Athena work,
I thought about a number of things.

37
00:03:35,980 --> 00:03:38,500
From this day forward, I'm Neo-Alice!

38
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:45,720
Sounds like you were inspired by
your mentor during Carnevale, too.

39
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:46,520
Yes.

40
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:48,660
You too, Aika?

41
00:03:48,660 --> 00:03:50,960
Yeah, I guess so. But...

42
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:56,960
...I've been working nonstop these
past few days, so I'm really... sleep... y...

43
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,630
Oh, Aika.

44
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:06,640
You're both really sleepy-heads...

45
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:17,210
Well, it is spring, after all.

46
00:04:20,420 --> 00:04:25,360
Say, why don't we get some coffee
at the café up ahead?

47
00:04:25,490 --> 00:04:27,260
Agreed!
Agreed!

48
00:04:32,970 --> 00:04:34,060
It's Al.

49
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:36,000
Huh? Al?

50
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:37,670
You're right.

51
00:04:37,670 --> 00:04:39,940
I wonder if he's having tea by himself...

52
00:04:39,940 --> 00:04:42,780
No... He's with Pony-boy...

53
00:04:42,780 --> 00:04:44,210
Yay!

54
00:04:44,210 --> 00:04:47,550
Al, Akatsuki!

55
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:55,860
How nice to see you all! Good morning.

56
00:04:55,860 --> 00:04:57,590
Good morning.

57
00:04:57,760 --> 00:05:01,530
