140
00:09:13,550 --> 00:09:14,450
My, my.

141
00:09:33,270 --> 00:09:34,700
We're back!
We're back!

142
00:09:35,170 --> 00:09:36,940
How did it go, President Aria?

143
00:09:36,940 --> 00:09:38,130
Did you catch any fi...

144
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:40,470
Oh, no!

145
00:09:40,470 --> 00:09:43,340
What happened, President Aria?

146
00:09:43,410 --> 00:09:45,400
Please pull yourself together!

147
00:09:56,360 --> 00:10:00,090
President Aria, could you
help us with this next?

148
00:10:01,930 --> 00:10:05,370
Alicia, I'll make the cookies.

149
00:10:05,530 --> 00:10:07,400
Yes, please do.

150
00:10:29,860 --> 00:10:31,330
Hello!
Hello!

151
00:10:31,330 --> 00:10:32,660
Coming!

152
00:10:32,830 --> 00:10:35,630
Oh, something smells delicious.

153
00:10:36,700 --> 00:10:38,390
Welcome!

154
00:10:38,930 --> 00:10:40,630
Please come upstairs.

155
00:10:40,970 --> 00:10:42,400
Coming in!

156
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:45,710
Thank you for inviting us today.

157
00:10:45,710 --> 00:10:47,440
My, my. Welcome.

158
00:10:47,440 --> 00:10:50,810
Athena's still working, but she said
she'd come when she's done.

159
00:11:06,430 --> 00:11:11,360
President Maa, President Aria's
pudgy-wudgy tummy isn't a snack.

160
00:11:13,530 --> 00:11:16,300
Okay everyone, let's have a seat.

161
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:18,940
Akari, could you bring the tea, please?

162
00:11:18,940 --> 00:11:20,300
Okay!

163
00:11:21,210 --> 00:11:23,510
So that's the cherry jam?

164
00:11:23,640 --> 00:11:25,510
I'm really looking forward to it.

165
00:11:25,510 --> 00:11:26,840
My, my.

166
00:11:27,380 --> 00:11:30,450
We've made a bunch of things,
so have as much as you like.

167
00:11:30,450 --> 00:11:33,390
Yay! Alicia's homemade cooking!

168
00:11:33,390 --> 00:11:34,860
We brought walnut bread, too.

169
00:11:34,860 --> 00:11:35,460
Thank you, Akira!

170
00:11:35,460 --> 00:11:36,490
Smells like spring...
Thank you, Akira!

171
00:11:36,490 --> 00:11:37,220
Smells like spring...

172
00:11:37,220 --> 00:11:40,290
All right! First, we need to
wash our hands and gargle.

173
00:11:40,290 --> 00:11:43,750
For Primas, keeping in good health
is an important part of the job.

174
00:11:43,830 --> 00:11:44,730
Right!
Right!

175
00:11:49,300 --> 00:11:51,790
All right, me first!

176
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:54,170
You're really a cheater!

177
00:11:54,640 --> 00:11:58,810
I can't lose to Pony-boy,
but I can't lose to Junior, either.

178
00:11:58,810 --> 00:11:59,910
Aika...

179
00:11:59,910 --> 00:12:00,750
Yes?
Aika...

180
00:12:00,750 --> 00:12:01,620
You're so childish.

181
00:12:01,620 --> 00:12:02,670
Wha-?!
You're so childish.

182
00:12:09,360 --> 00:12:11,090
It smells great.

183
00:12:11,160 --> 00:12:13,230
It makes it feel like spring, doesn't it?

184
00:12:13,230 --> 00:12:16,200
This is the first time I've had cherry jam.

185
00:12:17,770 --> 00:12:21,760
My, my. Did you want some
more tea, President Aria?

186
00:12:28,010 --> 00:12:31,010
Ah, you'd like more bread, too? Sure.

187
00:12:31,010 --> 00:12:32,310
My, my.

188
00:12:33,210 --> 00:12:39,450
Alicia, what kind of person was the customer
who sent you this cherry tea?

189
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:43,310
It was a mother and daughter
who were very close.

190
00:12:43,460 --> 00:12:45,580
Right, and also...

191
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:53,530
The building on your right is Palazzo Ducale.

192
00:12:53,530 --> 00:12:58,470
And straight across is the
Piazzetta of Piazza San Marco.

193
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:04,610
Once we leave this canal, the wind will
become colder, so please be careful.

194
00:13:05,050 --> 00:13:09,450
Neo-Venezia really is
a wonderful place, isn't it?

195
00:13:09,580 --> 00:13:12,550
You've always wanted to come here, Mother.

196
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:18,320
But I guess I should have brought you
when the weather was a little warmer.

197
00:13:18,990 --> 00:13:21,530
I chose a bad time to come.

198
00:13:21,530 --> 00:13:22,000
Not at all, I'm happy we came.
