Alice...

253
00:17:12,760 --> 00:17:14,560
Eh? What?

254
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:18,730
Were you just talking about me, Alice?

255
00:17:18,730 --> 00:17:21,440
Yes, about how you're really clumsy.

256
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:23,160
Ehh?

257
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:24,940
Welcome, Athena.

258
00:17:24,940 --> 00:17:27,110
Good work today!
Good work today!

259
00:17:27,110 --> 00:17:28,870
Thank you for having me!

260
00:17:30,910 --> 00:17:33,240
Which clumsy story?

261
00:17:33,610 --> 00:17:37,280
When I put mayonnaise on our pudding?

262
00:17:37,380 --> 00:17:41,880
Or when I slammed into the
glass door in the bathroom?

263
00:17:42,390 --> 00:17:44,120
No.

264
00:17:44,120 --> 00:17:48,530
Actually, we were talking about how
amazing the Three Great Water Fairies are.

265
00:17:49,860 --> 00:17:54,200
Sounds like the three of you realized
that you still have a long way to go.

266
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:58,270
We sure did. I feel kind of
depressed because of it.

267
00:17:58,270 --> 00:18:00,440
Let's do our best, Aika.

268
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:02,810
Of course we will.

269
00:18:03,980 --> 00:18:07,380
It's true that the three of you
have a long way to go.

270
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:10,440
Alicia.

271
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:13,950
But... so do I.

272
00:18:14,020 --> 00:18:18,290
Akira and Athena, too.
We all have a long way to go.

273
00:18:18,290 --> 00:18:19,260
Right?

274
00:18:19,530 --> 00:18:21,100
Yeah. You're right.

275
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:22,760
Eh?
Eh?

276
00:18:22,830 --> 00:18:25,170
That's really a shocker.

277
00:18:25,170 --> 00:18:28,100
You're already so amazing,
we could never catch up to you.

278
00:18:28,100 --> 00:18:29,470
She's right!

279
00:18:29,470 --> 00:18:33,010
So then, when are you going
to be satisfied with yourself, Akira?

280
00:18:33,010 --> 00:18:37,470
Probably... never,
no matter how much better I get.

281
00:18:37,710 --> 00:18:40,110
No matter how long I continue this job.

282
00:18:41,320 --> 00:18:47,350
If you believe you've reached the top and
become complacent, you can't move forward.

283
00:18:47,820 --> 00:18:53,160
That's why I think it's really important
to believe you still have a long way to go.

284
00:18:53,630 --> 00:18:54,620
Yes.

285
00:18:55,660 --> 00:19:01,140
"Tomorrow, I'll shine much
brighter than I did today."

286
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:04,000
That's something you want to
believe about yourself.

287
00:19:04,340 --> 00:19:08,110
That feeling will probably never change,
even if you become Primas.

288
00:19:08,110 --> 00:19:12,270
Even after you step off your gondolas for the
last time, that feeling will still be there.

289
00:19:12,710 --> 00:19:17,710
Maybe that's how everyone
finds their own brilliance?

290
00:19:18,250 --> 00:19:20,520
Their own brilliance...

291
00:19:20,520 --> 00:19:25,460
In other words, it's only natural
that you still have a long way to go.

292
00:19:25,590 --> 00:19:26,960
That's right.

293
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:29,720
And that's something very wonderful.

294
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:36,690
Maybe it's best to just cherish yourself and the
long journey ahead, and have fun along the way?

295
00:19:37,140 --> 00:19:38,430
Yes.
Yes.

296
00:19:38,940 --> 00:19:41,610
Hey Alicia, pour me another cup
of cherry tea, will you?

297
00:19:41,610 --> 00:19:43,910
Ah! Me, too.

298
00:19:44,710 --> 00:19:45,940
Yes, yes.

299
00:19:56,960 --> 00:19:59,980
I feel so relaxed after today.

300
00:20:00,190 --> 00:20:01,660
Yes.

301
00:20:01,660 --> 00:20:06,960
Alicia and the others will keep on chasing
after their own brilliance, won't they?

302
00:20:07,070 --> 00:20:09,560
I'm really motivated!

303
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:11,410
Do you remember?

304
00:20:11,410 --> 00:20:17,970
"If you can praise yourself honestly, and make
everything in this world something to enjoy..."

305
00:20:18,550 --> 00:20:24,040
"...then becoming the brightest
star Undine isn't a dream."

306
00:20:24,320 --> 00:20:27,350
Grandma taught us that, didn't she?

307
00:20:27,350 --> 00:20:29,020
I remember it.

308
00:20:29,620 --> 00:20:31,020
It's somehow...

309
00:20:31,020 --> 00:20:32,130
Yeah?

310
00:20:32,130 --> 00:20:33,460
Um...

311
00:20:33,460 --> 00:20:35,000
What is it?

312
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:36,720
How should I put it?

313
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:43,100
Our mentors, who we love so much,
teach us many precious things...

314
00:20:43,100 --> 00:20:47,570
...and always watch over us, just like the sky.

315
00:20:47,570 --> 00:20:48,770
Yes.

316
00:20:48,940 --> 00:20:54,400
I was thinking, maybe that's
something really special?

317
00:20:54,510 --> 00:20:55,850
Yeah.

318
00:20:55,850 --> 00:20:59,020
But we can't depend on it.

319
00:20:59,020 --> 00:21:05,860
Someday, we have to become the brightest stars,
so our own apprentices can say the same about us.

320
00:21:05,930 --> 00:21:07,360
Oh!

321
00:21:07,360 --> 00:21:09,700
Yeah... you're right...

322
00:21:09,700 --> 00:21:13,330
What's with that tone?
No being doubtful allowed!

323
00:21:13,330 --> 00:21:14,740
Huh?!

324
00:21:14,740 --> 00:21:17,870
You're Alicia's only apprentice!

325
00:21:17,870 --> 00:21:18,840
Yes...

326
00:21:18,840 --> 00:21:22,110
You need to be more self-conscious
and feel the pressure!

327
00:21:22,110 --> 00:21:23,080
O-Okay.

328
00:21:23,080 --> 00:21:25,910
You're really strict, Aika.

329
00:21:25,910 --> 00:21:29,450
We're definitely going to
become the brightest stars!

330
00:21:29,450 --> 00:21:30,580
Yeah!

331
00:21:31,450 --> 00:21:33,190
I can't hear you! Louder!
We're going to be the brightest stars!

332
00:21:33,190 --> 00:21:35,260
I wonder what kind of Primas they'll become?
I can't hear you! Louder!
We're going to be the brightest stars!

333
00:21:35,260 --> 00:21:36,820
I wonder what kind of Primas they'll become?
Yeah!!

334
00:21:36,820 --> 00:21:40,260
I wonder. But I'm looking forward to that day.

335
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:47,000
I'm looking forward to it too,
but that'll also be the day they leave us.

336
00:21:47,270 --> 00:21:49,360
It's kind of lonely.

337
00:21:49,970 --> 00:21:52,170
I'm sure Akira will cry.

338
00:21:52,170 --> 00:21:54,440
Wha-?! Who's going to cry?!

339
00:21:55,540 --> 00:21:56,940
My, my.

340
00:21:56,940 --> 00:21:58,570
Good grief.

341
00:22:00,250 --> 00:22:03,980
Though I'm sure each of them will be unique...

342
00:22:03,980 --> 00:22:08,720
...and become a new kind of Prima Undine
that we've never seen before.

343
00:22:08,960 --> 00:22:10,620
That's right.

344
00:22:10,620 --> 00:22:15,960
They'll become fairies, bringing
new wonders to Neo-Venezia.

345
00:22:16,030 --> 00:22:20,330
And then, the torch will be passed, won't it?

346
00:22:20,470 --> 00:22:21,870
Yeah.

347
00:22:23,570 --> 00:22:30,030
"Akari, it seems like spring in Neo-Venezia
helps bring out everyone's true colors."

348
00:22:30,810 --> 00:22:34,370
